troduced by them to England, displacing the Old English form <i>Æþelbeorht</i>. The name is popular in a variety of forms in Western Europe, and has been traditional in a number of European princely families. It was out of favour in England for centuries, however, and the revival of its popularity in the 19th century was largely in honour of  Queen Victoria's  consort,  Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha ."]}]},{"name":"Gwallter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Walter</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maredudd ap Gwallter was born about 1351, in Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom as the son of Gwallter ap Gwilym and Mrs. Gwalter Ap Gwilym. He had at least 1 daughter with verch Hywel Gethyr."},"et":{"about 1351–":"umbes 1351–Surnud","1351–Male":"1351–Surnud","1864–Female":"1864–Surnud","1355–Female":"1355–Surnud","1370–Female":"1370–Surnud","1415–Female":"1415–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1325–Male":"1325–Surnud","1415":"1415","1325":"1325","1864":"1864","1355":"1355","1351":"1351","1370":"1370","about 1351":"umbes 1351","Abercrychan, Llanymddyfri, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1351–":"noin 1351–Kuollut","1351–Male":"1351–Kuollut","1864–Female":"1864–Kuollut","1355–Female":"1355–Kuollut","1370–Female":"1370–Kuollut","1415–Female":"1415–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1325–Male":"1325–Kuollut","1415":"1415","1325":"1325","1864":"1864","1355":"1355","1351":"1351","1370":"1370","about 1351":"noin 1351","Abercrychan, Llanymddyfri, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1351–":"environ 1351–Décédé","1351–Male":"1351–Décédé","1864–Female":"1864–Décédée","1355–Female":"1355–Décédée","1370–Female":"1370–Décédée","1415–Female":"1415–Décédée","–Female":"Décédée","–Mal